# Renderer UI Conventions

- Use `React + Ant Design` as the default renderer stack, and prefer framework components before custom widgets.
- Route runtime operations through typed services (`services/daemonApi.ts`) and the Tauri host bridge (`window.waterayDesktop`); do not call core internals directly.
- Keep interactions asynchronous and resilient; surface daemon errors with clear, user-facing feedback.
- Keep page logic split by concern (`pages/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `services/`); avoid oversized multi-flow files.
- Use shared draft/notice patterns:
  - Draft toolbar + navigation lock: `DraftActionBar` + `useDraftNavLock`.
  - Operation notifications: `useAppNotice`.
  - Draft result notifications: `useDraftNotice`.
- Draft submit default is persist-only (`daemonApi.setSettings({ applyRuntime: false })`) unless runtime apply is explicitly required.
- Renderer code must not directly call Ant Design `message.success/error/warning/info`.
- Switch layout convention:
  - Forms/detail rows: left switch + right label (prefer `SwitchWithLabel`), help icon on label right.
  - Table cells: switch only, no repeated label text.
- Help tooltip convention:
  - Reuse shared `HelpLabel` / `SwitchWithLabel.helpContent`; do not build page-local `Popover + question-circle` helpers.
  - Help copy follows structured sections: default `使用场景 / 作用 / 注意` and optional `推荐`; when label meaning is already explicit, allow concise `作用 / 推荐`.
  - Use component-managed line breaks (`\n` or structured sections), and keep help icon on the label's right side.
- Static explanatory copy must not use persistent page-level `Alert`/banner blocks when the content is only mode explanation, usage notes, or other non-actionable help text that inflates layout height.
- Prefer attaching that guidance to the relevant label/control via `HelpLabel`, `SwitchWithLabel.helpContent`, or concise nearby helper text. Reserve `Alert` for runtime status, risk warnings, or actionable guidance that truly needs strong visual emphasis.
- Renderer icon source is `bootstrap-icons` via shared `BiIcon`; do not import `@ant-design/icons`.
- Keep style values tokenized/centralized; avoid repeated hard-coded spacing/radius/colors in JSX/CSS.
- Keep window chrome behavior (title bar/minimize/maximize/close) in dedicated components + host bridge utilities.

## Example

```text
BAD: page imports `antd/message` and builds local draft toast branches.
GOOD: page uses `useAppNotice` / `useDraftNotice` and shared draft hooks.

BAD: page shows a full-width `Alert` just to explain a mode or setting.
GOOD: page moves the explanation into `HelpLabel` / `SwitchWithLabel.helpContent` beside the related control.
```
